{"cursor":"13474","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n{{Infobox officeholder |name=Antony LEUNG Kam-chung |native_name =\n|native_name_lang = zh-hk\n| honorific-suffix = GBS, JP\n|image=Antony Leung - Annual Meeting of the New Champions Dalian 2009.jpg |birth_date= http://cablenews.i-cable.com/reference/people/ref-people-gov-\n0012.html |birth_place= Hong Kong |occupation=Chairman of the Blackstone\nGroup Visiting professor at the Nankai University |spouse=Fu Mingxia\n|alma_mater=Ying Wa College Universiity of Hong Kong Harvard Business\nSchool |office=Financial Secretary of Hong Kong |term_start=29 May 2001\n|term_end=16 July 2003 |predecessor=Sir Donald Tsang |successor=Henry Tang}}\n\n\n\n\n\n'Antony LEUNG Kam-chung' GBS JP (born 29 January 1952 in Hong\nKong with family roots in Shunde, Guangdong) was the former Financial Secretary\nof the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR). He now serves as the\nchairman of Blackstone Group's Asian office in Hong Kong.\n\nA former banker and civil service outsider, he took the top economic post in one\nof the world's key financial centres on 1 May 2001. Newspapers said Leung gave\nup a plump banker's package of more than HK$23 million (US$3 million)\na year for a more modest HK$2.45 million.\n","linknr":186,"url":"Antony_Leung","recorded":1375072374,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Antony_Leung&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Antony_Leung&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=fal